io.oasp.gastronomy.restaurant.offermanagement.common.api

Interface Offer

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ApplicationEntity, net.sf.mmm.util.lang.api.attribute.AttributeReadId<Long>, net.sf.mmm.util.entity.api.Entity, net.sf.mmm.util.entity.api.GenericEntity<Long>, MenuItem, net.sf.mmm.util.entity.api.MutableGenericEntity<Long>, Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    OfferEntity, OfferEto

    public interface Offer
extends MenuItem
    This is the interface for an Offer that combines Products with a price for the menu of the restaurant. The combined Products are a Meal, a SideDish, and a Drink. All of them are optional but at least one of the three has to be present in a valid Offer.

    • Method Detail

      • getNumber

        Long getNumber()
        Returns:
        the unique number of this Offer used in the menu. While the ID of an Offer is auto-generated and will never change, the number may be changed if the menu gets updated. This is the identifier used by customers to displace orders.
